- 'No officer involved arrests' refers to arrests where no officer is recorded as making the arrest;
- 'No officer involved arrest rate' is calculated as the percentage of total arrests that do not involve an officer.

- "ensnared by the law" refers to the total number of arrests;
- "average burden of charges" refers to the average number of total charges per arrest;
- "still under scrutiny" refers to pending charges;
- "let go" refers to dismissed charges;
